## Overview

Miller-Meeks faced an ethics complaint over where her primary address was actually located.

-   Leading up to the 2024 election, Miller-Meeks [changed her voter registration](https://www.desmoinesregister.com/story/news/politics/elections/2024/10/22/mariannette-miller-meeks-responds-to-ethics-complaint-about-voting-address/75204526007/) to an apartment in Davenport. -   It was [reported](https://www.kcrg.com/2024/09/24/ethics-complaint-alleges-rep-miller-meeks-voting-davenport-despite-living-ottumwa/) that Miller-Meeks used her Ottumwa address on official government forms. -   Iowa state law [required](https://www.thegazette.com/campaigns-elections/u-s-rep-mariannette-miller-meeks-davenport-apartment-linked-to-donor/) voters to register to vote at their primary address and vote in the county where they primarily resided.
